1
00:00:13,070 --> 00:00:16,620
Man, how long is Jaggy gonna sleep?

2
00:00:16,990 --> 00:00:18,790
We've got a problem!

3
00:00:18,790 --> 00:00:22,120
Inmate Eustass Kid escaped!

4
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:24,250
What?!

5
00:02:12,730 --> 00:02:15,360
Unbe-lick-able.

6
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:19,450
Mama just had to fall off
at the top of the waterfall!

7
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:23,790
King's aerial defense makes it
impossible to get back up there...

8
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:28,000
It's a miracle the Queen
Mama Chanter didn't capsize...

9
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:31,080
after falling from that height.

10
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:33,500
So, we just wait here or what?

11
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,210
For now.

12
00:02:35,210 --> 00:02:38,930
If we're thrown overboard,
anyone with powers will be incapacitated.

13
00:02:38,930 --> 00:02:42,010
No! Then, Mama sank into the sea?!

14
00:02:42,890 --> 00:02:44,220
Don't worry!

15
00:02:44,930 --> 00:02:46,970
Speaking of miracles...

16
00:02:46,970 --> 00:02:50,350
According to Mama's vivre card, she survived!

17
00:02:50,350 --> 00:02:52,860
Great! So she's alive!

18
00:02:52,860 --> 00:02:55,020
But then, where is she?!

19
00:02:55,020 --> 00:03:00,280
The Beast Pirates undoubtedly fished her out
and are already holding her captive.

20
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:04,080
By Kaido's crew? That complicates things.

21
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:07,160
Mama and Kaido used to be crewmates,

22
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:11,920
but they've grown adversarial
since becoming Emperors.

23
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:15,250
He'll definitely kill her.

24
00:03:15,250 --> 00:03:18,010
What?! Then what's gonna happen to us?!

25
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:20,640
Lickity-listen...

26
00:03:21,590 --> 00:03:24,430
The Big Mom Pirates will become...

27
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:29,480
the lickity Perospero Pirates!

28
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:31,600
Hey, what's the big idea, Peros?!

29
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:34,520
Our next captain has to be Katakuri!

30
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,770
Don't you give a lick about seniority?!

31
00:03:36,770 --> 00:03:38,780
Nonsense! Merit is more important!

32
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:41,360
The eldest son should lead!

33
00:03:42,570 --> 00:03:45,280
Do you want me to summon
my genie?! Don't think I won't!

34
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,780
Cut it out!

35
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:48,660
Don't just assume she's gonna die!

36
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:52,710
Never underestimate Mama, you morons.

37
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,960
Big Mom?

38
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:59,010
Yes, she's a super strong
person from overseas!

39
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:06,350
This sharkodile is a very
docile and sweet animal!

40
00:04:08,060 --> 00:04:11,310
You had to hit it twice to tame it!

41
00:04:11,310 --> 00:04:16,940
Wait! Why in the world would you need
to go to Udon with this Big Mom person?!

42
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:20,900
Because she's going to help us save Big Bro!

43
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:23,240
I-I do not follow!

44
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:26,700
Get back here, Otama! I need more details!

45
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:33,210
Sir Kin'emon instructed me
to guard Lord Momonosuke closely!

46
00:04:33,210 --> 00:04:36,170
It'll be all right, Master!

47
00:04:36,170 --> 00:04:40,630
As a kunoichi, I will protect Momo at any cost!

48
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:42,380
Who...? Who...?!

49
00:04:42,380 --> 00:04:46,260
Who's a kunoichi?!
Your skills are middling at best!

50
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:51,100
Stop being so reckless
and return immediately, Otama!

51
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:55,190
Sir Hitetsu, we have already departed.

52
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:58,020
What?! No, Lady Okiku...!

53
00:04:58,020 --> 00:05:00,020
Return this instant!

54
00:05:00,020 --> 00:05:02,240
Say "hi" to Komachiyo and the others!

55
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:10,580
By the way, did I hear you correctly
when you said "Big Mom" earlier?

56
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:12,500
That sounds familiar...

57
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,750
Forget about that, Olin!

58
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:18,920
Anyway, the people at
Okobore Town were so nice.

59
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:23,210
I was a stranger to them, and I
don't even know my own name,

60
00:05:23,210 --> 00:05:27,720
but that lady still treated me to
that sweet and delicious oshiruko...

61
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:33,180
The hat hasn't spoken at all.
Did it also lose its memory?

62
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:35,770
That reminds me...

63
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:39,360
I wanna have some more oshiruko soon.

64
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,770
Don't look at me when you say that!

65
00:05:40,770 --> 00:05:45,610
I can't help it. You're so cute
I could eat you up...

66
00:05:45,610 --> 00:05:47,860
I'm not food!

67
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:50,990
You're really pushing yourself, Momo!

68
00:05:50,990 --> 00:05:55,200
I am at the center of this conflict!
I must remain sharp!

69
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:57,710
SNATCH!

70
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:00,670
Oh, sorry! I apologize!

71
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:07,300
Say, why do you keep yelling "SNATCH"?

72
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:11,720
Saying SNATCH is really invigorating!

73
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,100
SNATCH!

74
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:18,100
SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!

75
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:21,400
You're right! I feel full of energy!

76
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,110
Right? Okay then!

77
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:25,780
– SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!
– SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!

78
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:27,860
Stop, both of you!

79
00:06:28,490 --> 00:06:29,240
Why, Kiku?

80
00:06:29,610 --> 00:06:31,370
Where did you learn that word?

81
00:06:31,370 --> 00:06:34,490
It is a rallying cry foreign swordsmen use!

82
00:06:34,490 --> 00:06:37,250
I learned it from Zorojuro!

83
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:40,920
He said it's a lucky word that
lifts your spirit when courage is lost.

84
00:06:41,380 --> 00:06:43,210
Well, this one forbids its use!

85
00:06:43,210 --> 00:06:45,960
What?! How come?!

86
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,880
It could be a coincidence,

87
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:51,140
but it also exists as a battle cry
from an old Kuri dialect.

88
00:06:51,140 --> 00:06:53,600
Its implications are inappropriate for you.

89
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,560
What?! Come on!

90
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,560
No!

91
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,980
But it's really invigorating.

92
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:01,190
No means no!

93
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:08,030
I'm hungry. Aren't we at Udon yet?

94
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:11,740
I'm so hungry I could...

95
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:14,200
Don't look at me when you're drooling!

96
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:18,660
Unfortunately, we are still far from Udon, Olin.

97
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:20,250
Is that right?!

98
00:07:21,790 --> 00:07:23,920
This is a rough map of Wano.

99
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:31,130
The six regions of the country all have
distinct climates and are divided by rivers.

100
00:07:45,940 --> 00:07:47,270
This is...

101
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:52,360
Shinobu's five color rice signal...
It says to check near the well...

102
00:07:54,410 --> 00:07:55,830
Is that where they are?!

103
00:07:57,450 --> 00:08:00,160
I am relieved that you are all still alive!

104
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:05,080
I did not expect you to have to flee
to Ringo to evade your pursuers.

105
00:08:05,570 --> 00:08:09,050
Orochi's men will not venture out this far.

106
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:13,970
The murder of Oiran Komurasaki
was quite shocking.

107
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:18,140
And now the Flower Capital is in an uproar.

108
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:24,850
Seriously, she was just standing up to Orochi.
How could he kill her so mercilessly?!

109
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:27,650
Samurai are scary...

110
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:32,110
Napping Kyoshiro was
the one who cut her down.

111
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:35,740
Kyoshiro? I am unfamiliar with that name.

112
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:41,120
Twenty years ago,
Wano's greatest yakuza boss...

113
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:44,250
was Hyogoro the Flower.

114
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:49,000
What a colorful name.

115
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:53,300
Boss Hyogoro valued honor
and championed the weak;

116
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:56,930
he would never have done
something so heartless.

117
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:03,770
Napping Kyoshiro... What a horrible man.

118
00:09:03,770 --> 00:09:08,440
Maybe we shouldn't have taken
Otoko back to Kyoshiro's pleasure hall.

119
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:11,190
Even though she upset the shogun,

120
00:09:11,190 --> 00:09:15,910
I have my doubts whether
this Kyoshiro will go after a child...

121
00:09:15,910 --> 00:09:21,080
But this guy offed his brothel's
most popular woman!

122
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,660
It worries me.

123
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:25,210
Let's head back to the Flower Ca–

124
00:09:26,210 --> 00:09:28,170
It's chilly, isn't it?

125
00:09:28,170 --> 00:09:30,670
Nice and warm! Thanks, Shinobu!

126
00:09:32,250 --> 00:09:35,170
Folks, if we're going back
to the Flower Capital,

127
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:38,890
why not rest our weary bones at a bathhouse?

128
00:09:38,890 --> 00:09:41,010
A bath sounds good!

129
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:43,470
That's right. We can freshen ourselves up.

130
00:09:43,470 --> 00:09:48,310
We'd have to sneak in with disguises.
Orochi regulates hot water and drinking water.

131
00:09:48,310 --> 00:09:51,610
In the Flower Capital, every single
aspect of life is controlled.

132
00:09:52,020 --> 00:09:57,780
But first, I would like to hear what information
you have collected so far, Lady Orobi.

133
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:03,080
Unfortunately, all I've collected so far is...

134
00:10:03,490 --> 00:10:06,710
what time Orochi will wake up
on the day of the battle,

135
00:10:06,710 --> 00:10:09,830
the offerings that they
will take to Onigashima,

136
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:13,000
Kaido's favorite food
and how his crew is organized,

137
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,960
the number of soldiers and weapons...

138
00:10:16,170 --> 00:10:17,630
That is a lot!

139
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:21,100
By the way, I discovered a poneglyph.

140
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:23,810
It wasn't a red one though...

141
00:10:23,810 --> 00:10:24,770
Really?!

142
00:10:24,770 --> 00:10:27,520
You sure are lucky with
those stones, Bonekichi!

143
00:10:27,980 --> 00:10:30,310
It was behind a reinforced
door in the basement.

144
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:33,860
It was a strange room full of wooden dolls.

145
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:39,360
That means the lode poneglyph needed
to reach Laugh Tale must be on Onigashima.

146
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:42,030
Onigashima, huh?

147
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:48,750
Mm-hmm. With this much information,
we can consider the mission a success.

148
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:53,250
Now, Orobi and Onami...

149
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:56,630
let's go to a bathhouse to
rest up and see some panties!

150
00:10:56,630 --> 00:10:58,670
You'd stand out too much!

151
00:10:58,670 --> 00:11:01,510
What?! Come on!

152
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:03,390
Breaking news!

153
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:07,640
The Flower Capital's top idol,
Oiran Komurasaki,

154
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:12,150
was cut down by Boss Kyoshiro
at the shogun's banquet!

155
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:15,150
You can read about it here!

156
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,660
Komurasaki my love!

157
00:11:23,660 --> 00:11:25,240
How could this happen?!

158
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:31,460
What's with the wailing?
You barely even saw her once.

159
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:34,000
The world lost a true beauty, dumbass!

160
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,090
The funeral will be held tomorrow.

161
00:11:36,090 --> 00:11:38,590
You're being insensitive!

162
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,220
The raid suit...

163
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:43,930
Do you think Orobi and the others got caught?

164
00:11:43,930 --> 00:11:48,810
I'm worried. Should I try
to contact them by smart snail?

165
00:11:48,810 --> 00:11:50,640
What do you think, Sanji?

166
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,690
The power of invisibility...

167
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:56,110
I guess I have to try it there...

168
00:11:56,110 --> 00:11:57,190
Hey, Sanji!

169
00:11:57,190 --> 00:11:58,780
In the women's bath!

170
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:01,950
Oh, yeah, you're right!

171
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:07,580
By the way, Traf, is there
any word on Udon and Luffytaro?

172
00:12:07,580 --> 00:12:11,710
Yeah, he's probably ready
to start a riot by now!

173
00:12:11,710 --> 00:12:14,580
For sure! I can't wait to see him again!

174
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:17,700
There's nothing on Straw Hat...

175
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:18,500
Wait...

176
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:20,210
Eustass?!

177
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:23,220
"You..." What?! "You" like the women's bath?!

178
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:23,970
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

179
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:28,220
Oh, you mean that guy's in Wano?!

180
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:33,520
Since his ally Hawkins is here,
it's no wonder that he's here, too...

181
00:12:34,310 --> 00:12:38,230
It seems he was being held at
the prison in Udon... and then escaped.

182
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:39,780
Escaped?!

183
00:12:39,780 --> 00:12:41,490
Hey, what about Luffy?!

184
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:45,610
I think something big is happening in Udon.

185
00:12:49,950 --> 00:12:50,740
By the way...

186
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:54,040
where's the bathhouse?

187
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:56,210
Dammit! Give it a rest already!

188
00:12:56,210 --> 00:12:58,540
You weren't listening at all!

189
00:12:58,540 --> 00:13:00,130
– You moron!
– You moron!

190
00:13:00,130 --> 00:13:01,420
Hey, wait!

191
00:13:02,970 --> 00:13:04,760
– What's going on?!
– What's going on?!

192
00:13:07,340 --> 00:13:09,310
I'm worried.

193
00:13:09,310 --> 00:13:12,270
Bepo's scouting party hasn't returned...

194
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:15,730
Let's hope it isn't more trouble.

195
00:13:21,110 --> 00:13:23,690
That's gross!

196
00:13:23,690 --> 00:13:25,400
Hey, you!

197
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:30,700
I need to ask you somethin'.

198
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:31,870
What?!

199
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:37,960
As you may have heard,
the prisoner Eustass Kid escaped!

200
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:40,540
I bet you know somethin'.

201
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:44,760
That reeks!

202
00:13:47,130 --> 00:13:50,760
It's been so long since
I've had this much to eat...

203
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:53,850
I am in your debt, Sir Straw Hat!

204
00:13:53,850 --> 00:13:58,400
I will... I will cherish every bite.

205
00:13:59,150 --> 00:14:00,440
Hey!

206
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:05,280
Let me have some!

207
00:14:05,740 --> 00:14:08,740
Those dumplings look delicious!

208
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:16,500
I'm sayin' that...

209
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:20,380
you had to have somethin'
to do with Kid's escape!

210
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:23,630
You guys were always talking!

211
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,260
His spit really stinks.

212
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:28,840
Stinks?! Are you mocking me?!

213
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:32,550
Don't forget you're wearing seastone cuffs!

214
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:37,390
Anyway, it's only a matter of
time before he gets caught!

215
00:14:37,770 --> 00:14:40,730
He clearly didn't think this jailbreak through.

216
00:14:40,730 --> 00:14:44,780
The moron still had his seastone cuffs on,

217
00:14:44,780 --> 00:14:48,740
so he won't get far before he's
hunted down and punished!

218
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:52,570
Cut it out! Your spit seriously smells!

219
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:55,660
You're really gonna keep testin' me?!

220
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:58,710
You need a refresher on the rules?!

221
00:14:58,710 --> 00:15:01,830
♪ Cross us once, lose your arms! ♪

222
00:15:01,830 --> 00:15:05,000
♪ Cross us twice, lose your legs! ♪

223
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,630
♪ Cross us thrice, lose your life! ♪

224
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:09,050
Idiot!

225
00:15:09,430 --> 00:15:12,680
You guys shouldn't screw with us!

226
00:15:17,890 --> 00:15:21,560
Stop hurting old man Hyo! You're killing him!

227
00:15:23,020 --> 00:15:27,900
Rules are rules. If you can't
keep up, you should die!

228
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:26,700
These millet dumplings... are precious...

229
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:29,860
Don't you agree?

230
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:30,990
The dumplings...!

231
00:15:31,410 --> 00:15:34,620
The rules say you can only eat
what you earn by working.

232
00:15:34,620 --> 00:15:38,000
If you can't work, you starve to death!

233
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,580
Isn't that right, old man?!

234
00:15:41,420 --> 00:15:43,960
Hey! You think you're getting away?!

235
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:47,340
Since you can't work,

236
00:15:47,340 --> 00:15:50,800
how did you get so many food tickets?!

237
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:52,220
Who gave them to you?!

238
00:15:52,630 --> 00:15:53,930
Dumplings...

239
00:15:54,340 --> 00:15:55,970
My dumplings...

240
00:15:55,970 --> 00:15:58,520
My precious dumplings...

241
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:01,350
You greedy old geezer!

242
00:16:08,610 --> 00:16:10,400
So good!

243
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,740
What do you think you're doing?!

244
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:17,620
You have no right to eat anything!

245
00:16:18,580 --> 00:16:21,120
No work? No dumplings!

246
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:23,920
Spit it out, you decrepit old coot!

247
00:16:26,710 --> 00:16:29,000
I won't spit them out...

248
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:33,930
Sir Straw Hat gave me these dumplings!

249
00:16:33,930 --> 00:16:37,470
I will never... ever...

250
00:16:37,470 --> 00:16:39,640
let them go to waste!

251
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:42,730
There! You should see this too!

252
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,400
Why?! That's gramps...!

253
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:52,530
It serves him right! The same will
happen to you if you cross us!

254
00:16:52,530 --> 00:16:54,490
Keep that in mind!

255
00:16:57,870 --> 00:17:00,450
Now, the truth about the dumplings!

256
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:04,830
Which bonehead gave you those tickets?!

257
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:10,800
I ate them!

258
00:17:11,550 --> 00:17:15,340
How far do you think you can push me?

259
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:18,560
I would rather die...

260
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:19,220
Huh?!

261
00:17:21,390 --> 00:17:23,100
...than tell a punk like you...!

262
00:17:23,770 --> 00:17:27,060
He answers the call of justice,
uplifting the weak...

263
00:17:27,650 --> 00:17:29,940
without ever yielding to fools...

264
00:17:30,940 --> 00:17:34,110
His is a truly chivalrous spirit,

265
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:39,030
deserving of honor from my own
chivalrous spirit, lest I dishonor myself!

266
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:50,960
Now, kill me!

267
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:56,340
Meeting him makes me nostalgic
for a bygone era.

268
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:01,970
I am Hyogoro the Flower!

269
00:18:03,140 --> 00:18:08,980
For the first time in ages,
my stomach and heart are full!

270
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:15,070
This is a land of samurai!

271
00:18:15,070 --> 00:18:17,990
In the old days,

272
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:20,280
many shared his spirit!

273
00:18:21,740 --> 00:18:24,580
But you went and killed them all!

274
00:18:27,330 --> 00:18:28,250
Hey!

275
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:30,210
Stop, Luffytaro!

276
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:36,590
You know what happens
when you defy the guards, right?!

277
00:18:37,090 --> 00:18:39,380
Kill me, you oaf!

278
00:18:40,970 --> 00:18:44,220
What was that?!
I dare you to say that again!

279
00:18:45,180 --> 00:18:52,020
I said that you are all brainless oafs
who can't help but resort to violence!

280
00:18:52,020 --> 00:18:53,690
You're an oaf!

281
00:18:54,470 --> 00:18:59,780
Unfortunately, we failed to defeat you oafs.

282
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:04,240
Right, since you said it again...
I'm gonna kill you!

283
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:09,460
Stop! If you assault a guard,

284
00:19:09,460 --> 00:19:12,830
they'll execute you on the spot, Luffytaro!

285
00:19:12,830 --> 00:19:14,210
Gramps!

286
00:19:14,210 --> 00:19:16,920
Hey! No! Don't do it!

287
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,380
Stop!

288
00:19:40,490 --> 00:19:42,280
Stop it...!

289
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:45,740
You have... to stop...

290
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:48,450
You can't keep...

291
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:52,870
making me cry...!

292
00:19:57,670 --> 00:19:59,630
Master Daifugo!

293
00:20:00,550 --> 00:20:04,590
Anyone that attacks a guard
is to be executed immediately!

294
00:20:04,590 --> 00:20:07,970
We saw it this time! You can't weasel out of it!

295
00:20:07,970 --> 00:20:09,310
Kill him!

296
00:20:09,310 --> 00:20:10,390
Yeah, kill him!

297
00:20:10,390 --> 00:20:17,570
– Kill him! Kill him! Kill him!
– Kill him! Kill him! Kill him!

298
00:20:17,570 --> 00:20:21,900
Master Solitaire! The keys have been stolen!

299
00:20:21,900 --> 00:20:25,070
Someone took a key
for a pair of seastone cuffs!

300
00:20:25,070 --> 00:20:29,160
What are you clowns doing?!
Didn't anyone see who did it?!

301
00:20:34,040 --> 00:20:36,670
A man with a big face crabbed them!

302
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:39,550
He got me to put a phony key in the safe.

303
00:20:39,550 --> 00:20:41,720
I was tricked, crab it!

304
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:47,180
Since I can only walk sideways,
he crabbed it right from under my nose!

305
00:20:48,510 --> 00:20:50,180
You dolt!

306
00:20:50,930 --> 00:20:52,390
You're an incompetent guard!

307
00:20:55,770 --> 00:21:00,650
He must still be in the tower!
Scour the place, including the attic!

308
00:21:04,150 --> 00:21:06,530
This is the essence of a ninja!

309
00:21:06,530 --> 00:21:09,910
I have the key!

310
00:21:09,910 --> 00:21:10,960
Halt!

311
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,620
It's an intruder!

312
00:21:15,210 --> 00:21:16,370
Afterimages?!

313
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:18,210
Stop, thief!

314
00:21:18,210 --> 00:21:20,210
It should have been sooner...!

315
00:21:20,210 --> 00:21:22,670
Sir Luffytaro, just a little longer!

316
00:21:23,130 --> 00:21:24,930
It's time to escape!

317
00:21:25,300 --> 00:21:28,760
Now I just have to slip away stealthily!

318
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:46,490
His Awesomeness!

319
00:21:48,870 --> 00:22:03,800
– Queen! Queen! Queen! Queen!
– Queen! Queen! Queen! Queen!

320
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:07,760
His Awesomeness, Superstar Queen, is here!

321
00:22:08,970 --> 00:22:11,050
Open the gate!

322
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:42,630
– Kill him! Kill him! Kill him! Kill him!
– Kill him! Kill him! Kill him! Kill him!

323
00:23:00,190 --> 00:23:02,770
What's with the racket?

324
00:23:20,370 --> 00:23:22,630
It's so tragic...

325
00:23:22,630 --> 00:23:25,000
There's no getting out of it this time!

326
00:23:25,420 --> 00:23:28,840
I won't forget you, Luffytaro!

327
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:31,180
This is the end for old man Hyo too!

328
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:37,970
You did great, Sir Straw Hat!

329
00:23:42,520 --> 00:23:44,690
Why are you talking like it's over?!

330
00:23:44,690 --> 00:23:45,740
Huh...?

331
00:23:45,740 --> 00:23:47,150
Let's get outta here!

332
00:23:50,530 --> 00:23:53,070
It's no use! Don't resist!

333
00:23:53,070 --> 00:23:57,040
What can you do when you're
weakened by seastone cuffs?!

334
00:23:57,910 --> 00:24:01,870
Shut up...! If you wanna fight...

335
00:24:01,870 --> 00:24:02,870
bring it on!

336
00:24:03,290 --> 00:24:05,540
What's the deal with that prisoner?

337
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,380
How is he able to fight so easily?

338
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:14,760
Regulations state that the seastone cuffs
shouldn't prevent the wearer from working.

339
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:18,520
But his movements should
still be severely impaired!

340
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:21,640
Are you saying that I'm still no match?!

341
00:24:22,020 --> 00:24:24,190
No, that's not what I meant!

342
00:24:27,730 --> 00:24:29,650
He's breathing heavily...

343
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:35,450
Warden!

344
00:24:36,410 --> 00:24:39,290
The seastone is working!

345
00:24:39,290 --> 00:24:42,540
He just has extraordinary resolve!

346
00:24:53,260 --> 00:24:59,560
It disturbs me how you're able
to defy the laws of physics.

347
00:25:03,020 --> 00:25:05,480
I consider it part of my training...

348
00:25:06,150 --> 00:25:10,400
to become even a little bit stronger
by the time I'm released from these!

349
00:25:14,650 --> 00:25:17,120
For someone without a future...

350
00:25:17,120 --> 00:25:20,950
what's the use in even trying?!

351
00:25:21,410 --> 00:25:25,080
Looks like I just found a sparring partner!

352
00:25:25,540 --> 00:25:27,210
You should know your place!

353
00:25:27,630 --> 00:25:30,800
Let's see you withstand my elephant's sneeze!

354
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:39,140
Elephant Achoo!

355
00:25:56,650 --> 00:25:59,910
Sir Straw Hat, are you okay?!

356
00:26:02,660 --> 00:26:04,620
Damn, he's strong!

357
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:09,540
Warden Babanuki!

358
00:26:09,540 --> 00:26:12,130
Superstar Queen arrived a bit ago!

359
00:26:12,130 --> 00:26:13,460
What?!

360
00:26:14,090 --> 00:26:15,920
Why didn't you tell me sooner?!

361
00:26:27,230 --> 00:26:31,400
If I get there before showtime, I'll kill you!

362
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:32,690
I'm sorry!

363
00:26:32,690 --> 00:26:36,190
Damn! If I could just use haki...

364
00:26:47,910 --> 00:26:49,500
My sweet Komurasaki...

365
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:53,130
You're so cute!

366
00:26:53,130 --> 00:26:55,710
Get excited!

367
00:26:55,710 --> 00:26:58,680
She's too good for Orochi!

368
00:27:07,310 --> 00:27:09,520
Komu-Womu... Komu-Womu...

369
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:11,310
O-Oh, yeah...!

370
00:27:11,310 --> 00:27:13,310
It's showtime.

371
00:27:13,310 --> 00:27:15,980
We'll stop by the pleasure hall later!

372
00:27:15,980 --> 00:27:17,610
Roger!

373
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:29,410
When should we tell him Komurasaki died?

374
00:27:29,410 --> 00:27:32,540
Never! We'd be the next ones to die!

375
00:27:36,130 --> 00:27:38,340
Here we go!

376
00:27:41,590 --> 00:27:43,430
♪ Zoom, zoom, zoom, zoom! ♪

377
00:27:43,430 --> 00:27:45,230
♪ Zoom, zoom, zoom, zoom! ♪

378
00:27:45,230 --> 00:27:47,190
♪ Zoom, zoom, zoom, zoom! ♪

379
00:27:47,190 --> 00:27:49,100
♪ Zoom, zoom, zoom, zoom! ♪

380
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:52,690
If I get thinner, I'll be too popular

381
00:27:52,690 --> 00:27:55,440
So I don't get thinner, that's my kind of...

382
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:57,440
funk!

383
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:03,820
♪ I may look chubby, but it's all muscle ♪

384
00:28:03,820 --> 00:28:06,450
♪ I can sing and dance, that's my kind of... ♪

385
00:28:06,450 --> 00:28:08,370
funk!

386
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:10,660
Get excited!

387
00:28:13,630 --> 00:28:15,500
Thanks for waiting...

388
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:18,250
you pieces of crap!

389
00:28:25,390 --> 00:28:26,930
Climb on!

390
00:28:26,930 --> 00:28:28,850
O-Okay...!

391
00:28:35,690 --> 00:28:37,610
Now then...

392
00:28:38,570 --> 00:28:41,990
Lay 'em on me one by one, Babanuki.

393
00:28:42,740 --> 00:28:46,700
Rank your biggest problems!

394
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,830
Number three!

395
00:28:52,830 --> 00:28:55,210
Eustass Kid escaped.

396
00:28:55,210 --> 00:28:57,590
What?!

397
00:28:59,090 --> 00:29:00,630
Number two!

398
00:29:00,630 --> 00:29:04,050
The key to a pair of
seastone cuffs has been stolen.

399
00:29:04,050 --> 00:29:06,590
What?!

400
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:09,310
And number one!

401
00:29:09,310 --> 00:29:12,810
Straw Hat Luffy is on the run.

402
00:29:13,350 --> 00:29:17,360
Whaaat?!

403
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:20,650
After him, you asshat!

404
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:29,080
Hey, it's no trouble whatsoever!

405
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:32,580
Feel free to use any of the empty houses!

406
00:29:32,580 --> 00:29:36,250
Anything for Young Master Zorojuro's friends!

407
00:29:37,790 --> 00:29:39,000
Thanks.

408
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,720
No need for gratitude.

409
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:45,220
The people here are literally dying of hunger,
so there are always empty houses!

410
00:29:46,180 --> 00:29:48,220
You really don't have to worry!

411
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:49,800
How is that funny...?

412
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:51,890
You sure laugh a lot.

413
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:58,860
When you're this hungry,
all you have left is laughter!

414
00:30:00,570 --> 00:30:04,570
Anyway, you just missed the Young Master!

415
00:30:04,570 --> 00:30:06,610
Where did he go?

416
00:30:06,610 --> 00:30:10,830
Well, he suddenly stormed out of here!

417
00:30:10,830 --> 00:30:14,160
Said something about his sword getting stolen!

418
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:16,710
There's no telling how far he's run...

419
00:30:16,710 --> 00:30:20,670
My money's on his getting
lost on his way back...

420
00:30:20,670 --> 00:30:22,000
As usual...

421
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:26,470
By the way, where did Black Leg go?

422
00:30:27,430 --> 00:30:29,640
When did we last see...?

423
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:32,060
That moron!

424
00:30:32,060 --> 00:30:34,520
The power of invisibility...

425
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:37,440
I guess I have to try it there...

426
00:30:39,310 --> 00:30:40,100
By the way...

427
00:30:41,900 --> 00:30:43,860
where's the bathhouse?

428
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:49,360
Don't tell me...

429
00:30:49,360 --> 00:30:51,120
he went there already!

430
00:30:56,500 --> 00:30:59,000
It's so relaxing!

431
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:01,630
So this is a Wanese bath?

432
00:31:01,630 --> 00:31:04,340
But isn't it a little too hot?

433
00:31:04,340 --> 00:31:10,550
But it's classy to tolerate the heat
and say, "The water is a bit chilly today."

434
00:31:10,550 --> 00:31:12,800
I guess I don't get the appeal...

435
00:31:14,140 --> 00:31:18,770
Orobi, do you dislike the heat?
Why don't you get into the hot water with us?

436
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:22,360
I'm not comfortable soaking
in a public bathhouse.

437
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:24,150
If anything happens...

438
00:31:24,150 --> 00:31:27,030
You're as cautious as a ninja!

439
00:31:27,030 --> 00:31:33,200
Magic users such as me and Orobi
get weaker when we soak in water.

440
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:35,910
But you shouldn't worry!
No foe will find us here.

441
00:31:36,790 --> 00:31:39,210
They may not be foes, but...

442
00:31:39,210 --> 00:31:41,750
Just look. Maybe I should charge them.

443
00:31:46,170 --> 00:31:47,800
I can't believe...

444
00:31:50,930 --> 00:31:52,260
it's a mixed bath!

445
00:31:52,970 --> 00:31:55,600
Yes, it is.

446
00:31:55,970 --> 00:31:59,930
Have you never come across
a mixed bathhouse like this?

447
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:08,860
Unsurprisingly, those men can't keep
their eyes off me, but it can't be helped!

448
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:12,700
All young men love...

449
00:32:17,740 --> 00:32:21,040
– Hey, move!
– Old lady, you're in the way!

450
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,580
Outta the way!

451
00:32:22,580 --> 00:32:25,790
– Move! Move! Move!
– Move! Move! Move!

452
00:32:25,790 --> 00:32:28,710
Ninpo: Ball Buster!

453
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:37,680
– That hurts!
– That hurts!

454
00:32:42,270 --> 00:32:44,480
Let's move to the washing area.

455
00:32:46,810 --> 00:32:50,610
When you're done warming up,
you ask Sansuke to wash your back.

456
00:32:50,990 --> 00:32:53,200
Who's Sansuke?

457
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:00,040
He's Sansuke.

458
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:03,750
It's what we call the one who
washes our backs at the bathhouse.

459
00:33:03,750 --> 00:33:05,670
Why an octopus?

460
00:33:05,670 --> 00:33:09,420
Well, he has eight limbs,
so he's suited to the job.

461
00:33:09,420 --> 00:33:14,220
Kyoshiro's one scary customer!
Who knows what he was thinking...?

462
00:33:14,220 --> 00:33:16,390
As if anyone knows what a yakuza thinks...

463
00:33:16,390 --> 00:33:19,060
What're you talkin' about, you idiot?!

464
00:33:19,060 --> 00:33:22,730
Wano's yakuza are supposed
to be for the people.

465
00:33:22,730 --> 00:33:26,600
Youngsters these days have
no idea that there was once

466
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:30,610
a great yakuza boss named
Hyogoro the Flower.

467
00:33:31,820 --> 00:33:34,950
Is that the man Kanjuro mentioned?

468
00:33:36,070 --> 00:33:40,450
Twenty years ago,
Wano's greatest yakuza boss...

469
00:33:41,410 --> 00:33:44,790
was Hyogoro the Flower.

470
00:33:45,830 --> 00:33:49,540
That's right. If Boss Hyogoro were still around,

471
00:33:49,540 --> 00:33:52,420
he could've instantly rallied every last samurai.

472
00:33:52,420 --> 00:33:57,260
I honestly doubt we'll be able to recruit
5,000 by ourselves within the week.

473
00:33:57,260 --> 00:33:59,350
Maybe 500, at most.

474
00:33:59,350 --> 00:34:02,770
Wow... He was that great?

475
00:34:02,770 --> 00:34:04,230
He was!

476
00:34:06,770 --> 00:34:10,770
Twenty years ago, he was the most
influential man behind the scenes in Wano,

477
00:34:10,770 --> 00:34:14,280
the great boss who controlled
the Flower Capital's underworld.

478
00:34:14,900 --> 00:34:18,610
He had pull among the five regional bosses...

479
00:34:18,610 --> 00:34:20,320
and treated the common man well.

480
00:34:20,320 --> 00:34:24,540
He was a truly chivalrous yakuza with
both power and charisma to boot.

481
00:34:25,370 --> 00:34:29,500
Lord Oden himself grew up respecting him.

482
00:34:29,500 --> 00:34:32,460
Then, if we can find him...!

483
00:34:32,460 --> 00:34:35,260
It's been over twenty years.

484
00:34:35,720 --> 00:34:38,970
Rumor has it...

485
00:34:41,180 --> 00:34:44,890
Orochi killed him for refusing
to work under the Kurozumi Clan!

486
00:34:47,060 --> 00:34:50,190
He's the opposite of Fukurokuju,
head of the Oniwabanshu.

487
00:34:50,190 --> 00:34:54,360
Like Boss Hyogoro, he also
supported the Kozuki Clan,

488
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:57,990
but Fukurokuju chose to serve Orochi instead.

489
00:34:57,990 --> 00:35:02,660
I worked for him back then,
but I couldn't take it and ran away.

490
00:35:03,370 --> 00:35:06,000
Indeed, I became their enemy!

491
00:35:06,510 --> 00:35:08,250
I see...

492
00:35:08,250 --> 00:35:09,800
Is that you...

493
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,000
Hanzo?!

494
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:14,880
So you're alive! The man-seducing...

495
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:17,050
sexy kunoichi.

496
00:35:17,130 --> 00:35:21,510
That's why Hanzo recognized you!
You're so cool, Shinobu-chan!

497
00:35:21,510 --> 00:35:22,680
I kind of am!

498
00:35:24,310 --> 00:35:26,270
I miss that man...

499
00:35:26,270 --> 00:35:28,390
Boss Hyogoro...

500
00:35:28,390 --> 00:35:30,770
He's become a part of history now...

501
00:35:32,270 --> 00:35:35,610
Tch...! You've given us a lot of trouble.

502
00:35:37,740 --> 00:35:40,910
Stop making me repeat myself...

503
00:35:40,910 --> 00:35:47,240
I'm telling you if you join our crew,
Kaido will pardon you for everything!

504
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:49,040
Shut up! I refuse!

505
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:54,420
What bad timing!

506
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:56,500
Sir Luffy...!

507
00:35:56,500 --> 00:35:58,010
I have the key!

508
00:35:58,010 --> 00:36:00,880
This is kind of nostalgic, Hyogoro!

509
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:05,970
Kaido-san and Orochi eagerly approached
you with a similar offer back then.

510
00:36:05,970 --> 00:36:11,480
To think that legendary yakuza is now
nothing but a malnourished old man.

511
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:14,650
And he'll die a miserable death!

512
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:19,190
What? Is he the Hyogoro?

513
00:36:19,190 --> 00:36:21,780
Get serious! That tiny old man?

514
00:36:22,610 --> 00:36:24,320
I don't care about myself...

515
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:27,950
but please spare this young man!

516
00:36:27,950 --> 00:36:29,370
I'm begging you!

517
00:36:29,910 --> 00:36:30,790
Please!

518
00:36:33,830 --> 00:36:35,460
What to do...?

519
00:36:37,460 --> 00:36:39,090
Okay, I've got it!

520
00:36:39,090 --> 00:36:42,300
I came up with an exciting idea!

521
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:44,140
Sir Luffy...!

522
00:36:44,140 --> 00:36:49,180
I cannot believe it. You really do
look the same as back then.

523
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:50,520
Who's that?!

524
00:36:50,890 --> 00:36:52,850
Is someone there?!

525
00:36:54,350 --> 00:36:56,730
It is I, Raizo...

526
00:36:58,360 --> 00:37:01,490
Is Lord Momonosuke safe?

527
00:37:01,990 --> 00:37:05,030
Is that you...

528
00:37:05,030 --> 00:37:06,870
Kawamatsu?!

